  <article>
    <articleinfo>    
      <title>AutoYaST2: Bugs and known issues</title>
      <author>
	<firstname>Anas</firstname>
	<surname>Nashif</surname>
      </author>    
    </articleinfo>
    <para>
    The following is a list of known bugs and issues with the auto-installation
    system in SuSE Linux 8.0.
    </para>
  <section>
    <title>Bugs</title>


<!-- bug start -->
    <refentry>
      <refnamediv>
	<refname>Configuration options missing in configuration system</refname>
	<refpurpose></refpurpose>
      </refnamediv>
      <refsect1>
	<title>Applies to</title>
	<para>SuSE Linux Version 8.1</para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
	<title>Severity</title>
	<para>Major</para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
	<title>Symptom</title>
	<para>
		When using the configuration system (<command>yast2 autoyast</command>) many configuration modules, i.e. partitioning 
		do not show up in the configuration tree.
	  </para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
	<title>Cause</title>
	<para>Missing file in RPM package</para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
	<title>Solution</title>
	<para>
		Install new package. 
	  </para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
	<title>Status</title>
	<para>Fixed, Update package <ulink
	    url="ftp://ftp.suse.com/pub/people/nashif/autoyast2/8.1/RPMS">available
	    on FTP server.</ulink></para>
      </refsect1>
    </refentry>

<!-- bug end -->


